data.title: Gerry Miller?

data.text:
I know he's not a Tele player and probably not well known but personally I've always loved the work this guy did with Moby Grape. Anybody else have any love for Jerry? This guy could play some blues as well as rock. He's still playing around Washington State and the west coast. I did see he had some adversity with the floods on December.

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oAUGyED5vH0

One of my all time favorite guitarists. He performed for a while with Bill Champlin as "The Rhythm Dukes" back in the late '60's. That was a great little band! Around '77 he had a band called "The Original Haze" with Michael Been, later of "The Call." I saw them one night and he noticed I was checking out his playing. Some guitarists seeing that would turn away from you. Jerry came over closer to where I was standing so I could see better. I love the sound of a big Gibson jazz box played through a cranked amp. Terry Haggerty of The Sons of Champlin was great in that respect, too.
